<br>
First of all, as a new barbarian, you are (Like any character) Going to Die.....A lot. First thing to do. Stay near the Halas Ramp/Newbie Zone. Dont bother wandering too much, exploration comes a little later. Your spawn point becomes the halas ramp naturally. Fetching a corpse thirty In game feet from you is a lot easier than searching around, Finding a SoW for a corpse run running around some more, Doing a few /ooc anybody seen my corpse? Make is easy for yourself. Stay near home.<br>
Secondly, and this is very important also. You don't lose XP for the first four or five levels of your character. So, if this is the case, Why fear death? Lets look at it carefully. Dying makes you loose any stuff you picked up. (Okay, if you followed the first thing, its almost in sight upon spawning) But on a positive note, it gives you five more food and water. Its better to stay in a fight and die. Dont run. No point, Dying is a good thing as long as your corpse isnt too far away. Also, if you are standing still, its easier for someone to come to your assistance (Anyone ever had to chase after three MOBS that were chasing another character that was fleeing? I have. Its a Pain.) Stand and fight. Besides , perhaps your skills will go up some more? Who knows?<br>
    Last thing, Loot everything. Scrounge. Dont leave anything on a corpse, you need every copper you can find to start out with. This includes stackable items like bone chips. Chartacters will pay a couple plat or so per stack of stuff like this. Dont be greedy, Nothing irks other players more than someone demanding 5pp a stack of something. They are paying for the right of not having to gather it themselves. Besides, they are more likely to help out someone who isnt greedy. Also, ruined pelts arent worthless, Do a couple of Shouts for new Tailors. Offer them the pelt if they will make you armor. Some will some won't Dont get discouraged. ( I spent four hours making armor for New characters later after someone did it for me. Got my skill up to 26 and met a lot of cool people)<br>
 QUESTS:<br>
<br>
First, Newbie Quests. Quests are VERY important. (Hint : Ever QUEST. I personally have found the name to be very similar to purgatory, scarey when you think about it. Pass the crack pipe will ya?) Here are a few that every new character should try to accomplish (Worth XP, Money, and Some other reward)<br>
<br>
Cantl<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> Located in Mac's kilts) This lady wants White polar bear skins. They are an uncommon drop off the polar bear cubs in the newbie zone) GIVE them to her and she rewards you with xp, a gold, and a piece of tattered armor) Dont knock tattered armor, this stuff will keep you alive longer to kill more stuff to get more xp, get it?<br>
<br>
Female Warrior trainer (In the Pit of Doom Warrior guid): (Dont remember her name offhand) She has a couple three quests. Most give okay xp rewards for new characters, but she is fairly stingy with her item rewards. One is Goblin Ice necklaces(six), Gnoll Fang (three), And Orc Wristbands (Four) You will probably not be able to do any of her quests until level four or higher, but just keep her in mind.<br>
<br>
There are lots more. Best site Ive found is Everlore.com for looking up quests. Check it out.<br>
<br>
<br>
Okay, now we get to what to kill,<br>
<br>
1st level - Decaying Sceletons, Gnoll Pups, Goblin Whelps. /con everything (Or right click on it) At first level, all other first level creatures will con white. <br>
<br>
2-3 Everything from First level, plus spiderlings and snow wolves. See if you cant get a better weapon from a skelleton. Even a rusty Longsword is better than that newbie shortsword POS. (I used A rusty longsword until sixth, No twinkage for me. But it worked just fine.)<br>
<br>
4-6 Kill everything in the zone. Polar bear cubs especialy, they give great xp. Collect everything , sell, Do some newbie quests. Get tattered armor. <br>
<br>
Sixth level, Congrats!!!! Time to think about travelling. Blackburrow (South of Everfrost Halas Ramp) Has a pretty good area for gaining xp and some halfway decent loot. gnoll fangs are very cool at your level, You get the xp for the gnoll, plus extra for turning in the fang (What a bargain!) Qeynos Hills just outside is also a good place to hunt. Either of those two places can easily get you to tenth or more if you are careful.  <br>
      If you are going to go far to hunt, get a bind affinity from a caster, as close as you can to where you are hunting. (Remember, Long Runs for Corpses SUCK. Anyone who has done a freeport to Qeynos or Karana's Corpse run w/o SoW will give you a sympathetic look for it. Bind close to wherever you decide to hunt.    <br>
     I wish you the best of luck in your adventures. I had a lot of luck, but there were a lot of friendly people from the Mithaniel Marr Server to help. Find them, befriend them, you wont regret it.<br>
